Package: mcc
Type: Package
Title: Mean Cumulative Count for Left-Truncated Competing Risks Data
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Grace", "Zhou", 
                  email = "grace.zhou@stjude.org", 
                  role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
                  comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-4084-9100"))
Description: Estimates the total burden of recurrent events within a population 
    using the Mean Cumulative Count (MCC) method. Specifically designed to handle 
    left-truncated data in the presence of competing risks by applying 
    time-dependent censoring and truncation weights, suitable for complex cohort 
    studies like the Childhood Cancer Survivor Study (CCSS).
